Type `quit` to exit this chatbot.
APR stands for Annual Percentage Rate. It is a measure of the total cost of borrowing money, including interest and fees, over a one-year period. It is expressed as a percentage and represents the amount of money that a borrower would pay in interest over the course of a year if they were to borrow the principal amount on a loan for one year.




